# --require -e=FILENAME_PATTERN         # file must exist
# --require -r=FILENAME_PATTERN         # file must be readable
# --hard                                # links treated as hard
--alias VSEQ=VIRTUAL_SEQUENCE
--alias VSQR=VIRTUAL_SEQUENCER

# BRIEF
#! Creates a new UVM test component

=pod

=head1 NAME

B<uvm-test template> - Creates a new UVM test component

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<new> uvm-test I<OPTIONS> {:I<NAME>:} [{:I<PARAMETERS>:}]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

Creates a basic UVM test class.

=head1 PARAMETERS

=over

=item {:B<VIRTUAL_SEQUENCE>:}={:I<UVM_VIRTUAL_SEQUENCE_CLASS>:}

The class name of the UVM virtual sequence to use as the main sequence.
Often a virtual sequence. Aka B<VSEQ>.

=item {:B<VIRTUAL_SEQUENCER>:}={:I<UVM_VIRTUAL_SEQUENCE_CLASS>:}

The class prefix name of the UVM virtual sequencer to use for the main
sequence. Often a virtual sequence.  Optional. If not specified, null
sequencer will be assumed. Aka B<VSQR>.

=back

=head1 REQUIREMENTS

UVM 1.1d or later.

